sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist<br/>Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as Jupyter Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP (internal)
    participant PyPI as pypi.org<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Elyra as Kubeflow Pipelines API<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant RuntimePod as Runtime Pod<br/>(Elyra Pipeline)

    %% Flow 1: User Accesses Workbench
    Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: User Accesses Workbench via Browser
    User->>Router: GET /notebook/{namespace}/{username}/<br/>No auth (initial request)
    Router->>OAuth: Forward to oauth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    OAuth->>OAuthServer: OAuth redirect<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    OAuthServer-->>OAuth: OAuth token
    OAuth->>Jupyter: Forward to Jupyter Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP (internal)<br/>OAuth validated
    Jupyter-->>OAuth: JupyterLab HTML/JS
    OAuth-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: 200 OK<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Session cookie set

    %% Flow 2: Install Python Package
    Note over User,PyPI: Flow 2: Install Python Package from Workbench
    User->>Jupyter: Terminal: pip install pandas<br/>or uv add pandas
    Jupyter->>PyPI: HTTPS GET /simple/pandas<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>No auth
    PyPI-->>Jupyter: Package index + download URL
    Jupyter->>PyPI: Download package wheel<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    PyPI-->>Jupyter: Package .whl file
    Note over Jupyter: Install to workbench filesystem<br/>UID 1001 permissions

    %% Flow 3: Access Data from S3
    Note over User,S3: Flow 3: Access Data from Notebook (S3)
    User->>Jupyter: Execute notebook cell:<br/>import boto3<br/>s3.get_object(...)
    Jupyter->>S3: HTTPS GET /bucket/data.csv<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM credentials
    S3-->>Jupyter: CSV data
    Jupyter-->>User: Display data in notebook

    %% Flow 4: Run Elyra Pipeline
    Note over Jupyter,RuntimePod: Flow 4: Run Elyra Pipeline Node (Runtime Image)
    Jupyter->>Elyra: POST /api/submit_pipeline<br/>8888/TCP HTTP<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Elyra->>K8sAPI: Create Pod (runtime image)<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    K8sAPI-->>RuntimePod: Pod created
    RuntimePod->>S3: Load training data<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS credentials from secret
    S3-->>RuntimePod: Data artifacts
    Note over RuntimePod: Execute pipeline node<br/>(train model, transform data, etc.)
    RuntimePod->>S3: Save results<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    S3-->>RuntimePod: 200 OK
    RuntimePod-->>Elyra: Pipeline node complete
    Elyra-->>Jupyter: Pipeline status update
    Jupyter-->>User: Display pipeline results
